On May 20, 2009, the White House sent several nominations to the Senate. Bartholomew Chilton of Maryland was nominated to be a Commissioner of the Commodity Futures Trading Commission. Colin Scott Cole Fulton, also from Maryland, was nominated to be an Assistant Administrator of the Environmental Protection Agency. Alejandro N. Mayorkas from California was nominated to be the Director of United States Citizenship and Immigration Services, Department of Homeland Security. These nominations were made to fill positions that were vacant or expiring.